@page "/demos/quote"

<PageTitle>Quote Component Demo</PageTitle>

<Container Size="ContainerSize.Size2">
    <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="8">
        <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size8">Quote Component Demo</Heading>
        
        @* Basic Example *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Basic Usage</Heading>
            <Text>
                His famous quote, <Quote>Styles come and go. Good design is a language, not a style</Quote>, 
                elegantly sums up Massimo's philosophy of design.
            </Text>
        </Flex>
        
        @* Multiple Quotes in Text *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Multiple Quotes</Heading>
            <Text>
                When asked about her inspiration, she said <Quote>Art is not what you see, but what you make others see</Quote>.
                Later, she added <Quote>Every artist was first an amateur</Quote>, encouraging young creators.
            </Text>
        </Flex>
        
        @* Truncate Example *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Truncated Quote</Heading>
            <Flex MaxWidth="300px">
                <Text>
                    <Quote Truncate="true">
                        The goal of typography is to relate font size, line height, and line width 
                        in a proportional way that maximizes beauty and makes reading easier and more pleasant.
                    </Quote>
                </Text>
            </Flex>
        </Flex>
        
        @* Wrap Options *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Wrap Options</Heading>
            
            <Box>
                <Text Size="TextSize.Size2" Weight="TextWeight.Bold" Mb="2">Wrap (default)</Text>
                <Box MaxWidth="250px" P="3" Style="border: 1px solid var(--gray-6);">
                    <Text>
                        <Quote Wrap="QuoteWrap.Wrap">
                            This is a very long quote that demonstrates how text wrapping works with different wrap options
                        </Quote>
                    </Text>
                </Box>
            </Box>
            
            <Box>
                <Text Size="TextSize.Size2" Weight="TextWeight.Bold" Mb="2">Nowrap</Text>
                <Box MaxWidth="250px" P="3" Style="border: 1px solid var(--gray-6); overflow: auto;">
                    <Text>
                        <Quote Wrap="QuoteWrap.Nowrap">
                            This is a very long quote that demonstrates how text wrapping works with different wrap options
                        </Quote>
                    </Text>
                </Box>
            </Box>
            
            <Box>
                <Text Size="TextSize.Size2" Weight="TextWeight.Bold" Mb="2">Pretty</Text>
                <Box MaxWidth="250px" P="3" Style="border: 1px solid var(--gray-6);">
                    <Text>
                        <Quote Wrap="QuoteWrap.Pretty">
                            This is a very long quote that demonstrates how text wrapping works with different wrap options
                        </Quote>
                    </Text>
                </Box>
            </Box>
            
            <Box>
                <Text Size="TextSize.Size2" Weight="TextWeight.Bold" Mb="2">Balance</Text>
                <Box MaxWidth="250px" P="3" Style="border: 1px solid var(--gray-6);">
                    <Text>
                        <Quote Wrap="QuoteWrap.Balance">
                            This is a very long quote that demonstrates how text wrapping works with different wrap options
                        </Quote>
                    </Text>
                </Box>
            </Box>
        </Flex>
        
        @* In Different Contexts *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">In Different Contexts</Heading>
            
            <Card Size="CardSize.Size2">
                <Text>
                    The architect famously stated: <Quote>Less is more</Quote>, 
                    which became a fundamental principle of minimalist design.
                </Text>
            </Card>
            
            <Callout Size="CalloutSize.Size2">
                <Text>
                    Remember: <Quote>The best way to predict the future is to invent it</Quote> - Alan Kay
                </Text>
            </Callout>
        </Flex>
        
        @* With Emphasis *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">With Emphasis</Heading>
            <Text>
                The speaker emphasized <Strong><Quote>Quality is not an act, it is a habit</Quote></Strong>, 
                reminding us that excellence comes from consistent practice.
            </Text>
        </Flex>
        
        @* Nested Quotes *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Nested Quotes</Heading>
            <Text>
                She recalled her mentor saying, <Quote>As Picasso once said, 
                <Quote>Good artists copy, great artists steal</Quote>, 
                but I believe great artists transform</Quote>.
            </Text>
        </Flex>
        
        @* With Different Text Sizes *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Different Text Sizes</Heading>
            
            <Text Size="TextSize.Size1">
                Small text with <Quote>a small quote</Quote> inline.
            </Text>
            
            <Text Size="TextSize.Size3">
                Regular text with <Quote>a regular quote</Quote> inline.
            </Text>
            
            <Text Size="TextSize.Size5">
                Large text with <Quote>a large quote</Quote> inline.
            </Text>
        </Flex>
        
        @* Real-World Examples *@
        <Flex Direction="FlexDirection.Column" Gap="3">
            <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size4">Real-World Examples</Heading>
            
            <Box>
                <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size3" Mb="2">Article Quote</Heading>
                <Text>
                    In her latest book, the author writes about the importance of perseverance: 
                    <Quote>Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts</Quote>. 
                    This message resonates throughout the entire narrative.
                </Text>
            </Box>
            
            <Box>
                <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size3" Mb="2">Product Review</Heading>
                <Text>
                    The customer said <Quote>This is the best product I've ever used</Quote> 
                    and gave it a 5-star rating. Another reviewer added, 
                    <Quote>Worth every penny</Quote>.
                </Text>
            </Box>
            
            <Box>
                <Heading Size="HeadingSize.Size3" Mb="2">Documentation</Heading>
                <Code>
                    The API documentation states: <Quote>All requests must include an authentication token</Quote>.
                    See the authentication section for details.
                </Code>
            </Box>
        </Flex>
    </Flex>
</Container>